The paper proposes a new model that combines neuroevolution and coevolution in the coordination of the GAN training algorithm. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The proposed model also aims to improve the training stability and the automatic discovery of efficient network architectures for GANs, which are topics related to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed model is evaluated in the MNIST dataset, which is a common dataset used in computer vision tasks, suggesting that the paper could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also uses adversarial characteristics between the generator and discriminator components, which is a topic related to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm using coevolution techniques, which is a topic related to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
